shed potatoes are meant to be eaten hot. ?The 4 jaga dangos were served on top of 2 white pieces of paper on a black plate, with a small side dish of salt, but not enough salt. I would suggest putting the tiny dish of salt in the middle of the 4 jaga dangos&MORE salt so it would be easier to get the salt. Interesting concept, but there were more batter than mashed potatoes. ?I liked the simplicity of it & the change in taste as soon as you add salt to it. Try it w/ & w/o the salt, it tastes like you're eating 2 diff. things! 5) BUTA KAKUNI: Another salty dish that my taste-buds liked!T his dish came w/ a REAL spoon! ?The pork had a great texture, delicious, tender, & even though it was in broth, the pork itself was juicy & not bland nor overcooked. I suggest to use less broth so the pork belly can stand out in the bowl more. 6) GYUTAN YAWARAKA NI: The presentation was wonderful, simple, & elegant. Hands down, one of the most fun dishes and experiences with food I've ever had! you get to cook the meat yourself! Once the waiter demonstrated how to work this dish before leaving us to it by ourselves, you'll be hoping more restaurants did stuff like this. ?Aside from the presentation and mini cooking exp, the beef tongue was lean, had a great texture when you bite into it, & very soft. If you squeeze some lemon juice while its cooking, the meat will become juicier and much more tender. LOVED It! 7) HOMEMADE " NIHACHI SOBA": The soba was served on a square plate & on a mini sushi wooden mat w/ shredded seaweed as the garnish, w/ individual dipping sauces, wasabi, & scallion. ?Great presentation itself. The soba was cooked perfectly so you won't have the exp. of it constantly breaking when you pick it up with your chopsticks if its overcooked, neither would have to chew through it if its undercooked. ?I suggest to give more wasabi. Some patons might like it more spicy. 8)HIRAME PONZU: Beautiful & careful presentation, & each sashimi slices were equal in size & had the right thickness so its not like putting a slab of goo in your mouth. Adding the diced scallion & roe on the sashimi gave it a good crunch when you eat it. 9)CHOCOLATE SOUFFLE: First time having a souffle & I was quite amazed. The chemistry of sweet hot melted dark chocolate mixed w/ the lightness of egg whites easily made me enjoy this dessert. ?It had a great balance in that the dark chocolate did not overwhelm so it would be bitter. Delicious! 10)BLACK SESAME CREME BRULEE: first time ever having creme brulee & i enjoyed every spoonful of it but eating the sugar torched top was the equivalent of someone asking for other people's pizza crust. You just want more of that ONE thing from it bc its what makes that dish so special, flavorful, & fun. The black sesame ice cream & thing on top of the creme brulee also gives a very aromatic aftertaste that kicks your senses. Great quality food & dining experience. Highly recommended!
