st thing before dessert was the cold buckwheat noodles with dipping sauce. ?This were cooked perfectly. ?I couldn't have asked for a better end to our gut-stuffing meal. Since it was my birthday dinner, my friend insisted on dessert. ?We got: Black Sesame Creme Brulee - my pick. ?Delicious, creamy, rich. ?Each spoonful was like a nibble of heaven. ?Too bad dinner was so filling, because I think I might've picked up the bowl and licked it clean - hahahhaha! ?I probably had half of it and was really saddened to leave it. Green Tea Ice Cream - I didn't even bother to try this, but I'm sure this was a premium version and not one of those where you can barely taste the green tea flavor. The presentation of all the dishes was impeccable. ?As was the service. ?Even with two dishes that bombed, it completely deserves my 5 stars. I also ran out of room, so I'm forced to cut my review short... ?But, know this, I *HEART* Sakagura!
