e picture I took), but I don't think it was too remarkable either (nor can I find something about it on the current online menu). The second sake bottle came out, as well as the eggplant (sanshoku nasu dengaku). ?It was less dry, and equally refreshing. ?The miso (of the eggplant dish) had a great flavor that cleansed the gritty nuts of the previous dish. Our final dish was a bit of a disappointment -- a bowl of hot udon. ?The udon had... vermicelli noodles it seemed like. ?I've never had udon noodles that thin. ?Also, the soup was rather insipid. ?But the warmth of the noodles did wash the meal down satisfactorily, and I walked out very happy. If I'm ever back in town, I'd definitely come back to try the other items on the menu. ?This easily ranks as one of my favorite meals. p.s. as I walked out, the sake really hit... and when I got off the train, I told my cousin to keep walking as I dashed to the nearest trash can to throw up. ?All in all, a great night =)
